{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Nevertheless, recent studies have provided empirical evidence on the extent of AI use in peer review.",
    "A commercial LLM detection service estimated that at least 15.8% of reviews for an AI conference were written with AI assistance [12].",
    "Liang et al. [13] developed a corpus-level detection model based on word distribution patterns and demonstrated LLM modification rates of 6.5% to 16.9% in AI conference peer reviews.",
    "In contrast, a similar analysis of journals in the Nature journals showed no significant evidence of LLMbased modifications, suggesting that the use of AI tools varies widely across academic disciplines.",
    "Current performance of LLMs in the peer review processRecent studies evaluating LLM capabilities in peer review tasks have shown mixed results across different assessment methodologies."
  ],
